- Document current styling inconsistencies, including layout and navigation issues
- Analyze unclear 3rd pane usage and inconsistent formatting
- Map out complete scope of changes needed
- Analyze complex layouts and interactive elements

### Phase 2: Layout and Structure Rationalization (1.5 hours)
- Determine clear purpose for 2-pane vs 3-pane layouts
- Standardize panel structure across all AI Manager pages
- Resolve formatting inconsistencies
- Ensure logical content organization in all panes

### Phase 3: Core Dashboard Updates (2 hours)
- Complete the main dashboard styling updates with neon blue theme
- Ensure all cards, charts, and data displays match theme
- Update navigation and sidebar elements with consistent styling
- Implement standardized button and form styling

### Phase 4: Cross-Page Consistency (2 hours)
- Apply theme to all related AI Manager pages
- Standardize navigation behavior and styling across pages
- Update shared elements and ensure consistent user experience
- Ensure responsive design consistency

### Phase 5: Advanced Features & Final Testing (1-2 hours)
- Handle complex interactive elements (charts, graphs, real-time updates)
- Test across browsers and devices
- Verify accessibility and performance
- Final consistency and usability checks

